1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:02,836
[Marcus] <i>They don't just have Datu Rahman.</i>

2
00:00:02,919 --> 00:00:04,337
<i>They also know our every move.</i>

3
00:00:04,421 --> 00:00:06,214
[in English] <i>We have an internal breach.</i>

4
00:00:06,297 --> 00:00:08,717
If you're wrong, then your career is over.

5
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:11,886
[Marcus] <i>Whoever is behind</i>
<i>all these killings,</i>

6
00:00:11,970 --> 00:00:13,596
<i>I will catch you.</i>

7
00:00:13,680 --> 00:00:18,935
<i>If no one did enter and exit</i>
<i>before Usman and I arrived,</i>

8
00:00:19,019 --> 00:00:20,520
<i>it's possible he wasn't</i>
<i>transferred at all.</i>

9
00:00:20,603 --> 00:00:22,230
<i>We were just looking at the wrong place.</i>

10
00:00:22,313 --> 00:00:24,399
<i>If this isn't in the original blueprint,</i>

11
00:00:24,482 --> 00:00:26,443
<i>it is possible</i>
<i>that they're hiding something.</i>

12
00:00:26,526 --> 00:00:29,738
- [grunts]
- [thuds]

13
00:00:31,322 --> 00:00:34,367
- [gunshots]
- [grunts]

14
00:00:34,451 --> 00:00:36,453
Move Datu Rahman right now!

15
00:00:37,412 --> 00:00:39,164
[gunshots]

16
00:00:39,247 --> 00:00:41,082
[Marcus] They came for you! Let's go!

17
00:00:41,916 --> 00:00:42,751
‪[tires screeching]

18
00:00:45,295 --> 00:00:46,296
[Lara breathes heavily]

19
00:00:46,379 --> 00:00:48,673
[Lara] <i>How could this happen?!</i>

20
00:00:48,757 --> 00:00:50,216
[Lara gasping]

21
00:00:50,300 --> 00:00:52,343
Who took you?! Who?!

22
00:00:55,889 --> 00:00:57,098
[grunts]

23
00:00:57,182 --> 00:00:58,933
[Jalil groans]

24
00:00:59,851 --> 00:01:01,519
You're coming with us.

25
00:01:01,603 --> 00:01:03,480
[Marcus] <i>Let's not make this</i>
<i>any longer, Datu Rahman.</i>

26
00:01:03,563 --> 00:01:06,733
Who abducted you when you
were transferring facilities?

27
00:01:06,816 --> 00:01:08,902
- What were they planning to do with you?
- [scoffs]

28
00:01:08,985 --> 00:01:11,696
No one should know
that we have Datu Rahman.

29
00:01:11,780 --> 00:01:13,865
[Marcus] <i>He's the key to all this chaos.</i>

30
00:01:13,948 --> 00:01:17,160
<i>As long as we have him, we have leverage.</i>

31
00:01:17,243 --> 00:01:19,996
[Manuel] <i>You can't</i>
<i>even do one thing right.</i>

32
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:22,499
Did you know that the Muslim Affairs

33
00:01:22,582 --> 00:01:25,460
is now watching you closely?

34
00:01:25,543 --> 00:01:29,464
[Manuel] <i>They're planning</i>
<i>to send an officer</i>

35
00:01:29,547 --> 00:01:31,466
<i>to monitor everything.</i>

36
00:01:32,050 --> 00:01:34,052
Are there any news on Brother Jalil?
[soft sobbing]

37
00:01:34,135 --> 00:01:34,969
Not yet.

38
00:01:35,678 --> 00:01:37,180
[Omar] <i>Let's put our faith in Allah,</i>

39
00:01:37,263 --> 00:01:38,765
<i>that he's safe wherever he may be.</i>

40
00:01:38,848 --> 00:01:41,476
[suspenseful music playing]

41
00:01:51,027 --> 00:01:56,866
[mysterious theme music playing]

42
00:02:12,090 --> 00:02:14,717
- [Manuel] Huh.
- [Ahmad] General!

43
00:02:15,385 --> 00:02:16,219
[suspenseful music playing]

44
00:02:16,302 --> 00:02:18,429
- General Carillo.
- [Manuel] Ahh…

45
00:02:18,513 --> 00:02:19,597
Professor Mustapha.

46
00:02:19,681 --> 00:02:21,766
[huffs] I am no longer a professor.

47
00:02:21,850 --> 00:02:24,769
[scoffs] I've been retired
for a while now, too.

48
00:02:25,770 --> 00:02:28,815
I'm guessing you know why
the president called for you.

49
00:02:28,898 --> 00:02:29,774
Yes.

50
00:02:29,858 --> 00:02:32,735
He's concerned about the high number

51
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:34,612
of illegal weapons cases
across the country.

52
00:02:34,696 --> 00:02:35,989
[exhales, in English] I am aware.

53
00:02:36,573 --> 00:02:39,492
But don't worry, Ahmad.

54
00:02:39,576 --> 00:02:43,913
I'll help the president
assess the situation.

55
00:02:43,997 --> 00:02:47,083
We need to protect the president.

56
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:48,835
His rating's falling.

57
00:02:49,627 --> 00:02:52,463
Not just the president, Ahmad.

58
00:02:52,547 --> 00:02:56,259
We need to protect the Republic.

59
00:02:56,926 --> 00:02:57,886
[Ahmad chuckles softly]

60
00:02:57,969 --> 00:02:59,095
[in English] Of course.

61
00:02:59,804 --> 00:03:02,223
- [in English] General.
- [in English] Thank you.

62
00:03:07,645 --> 00:03:09,397
[stirring music playing]

63
00:03:11,065 --> 00:03:12,108
[Manuel] Ah…

64
00:03:13,318 --> 00:03:14,152
‪[music concludes]

65
00:03:16,321 --> 00:03:17,614
[lock clanging]

66
00:03:21,993 --> 00:03:23,411
[Marcus] Datu Rahman.

67
00:03:23,494 --> 00:03:24,454
[unsettling music playing]

68
00:03:25,121 --> 00:03:27,790
[sighs] I looked for you in the census.

69
00:03:29,375 --> 00:03:33,004
There is no registered Rahman Abubakar.

70
00:03:34,881 --> 00:03:36,758
That's not your real name.

71
00:03:39,802 --> 00:03:41,095
Who are you?

72
00:03:41,179 --> 00:03:43,890
If you have to ask that question…

73
00:03:46,392 --> 00:03:48,019
then it means…

74
00:03:49,312 --> 00:03:52,565
you're not doing your job well.

75
00:03:53,149 --> 00:03:55,151
What exactly is your job?

76
00:03:55,652 --> 00:03:59,447
Do the people you serve
know that you have me?

77
00:04:01,199 --> 00:04:02,242
[loud thud]

78
00:04:04,494 --> 00:04:07,538
Don't you see? Huh?

79
00:04:08,581 --> 00:04:10,250
I saved you!

80
00:04:11,334 --> 00:04:14,712
If there's someone you can trust, it's me.

81
00:04:15,463 --> 00:04:18,424
This could all just be for show.

82
00:04:19,676 --> 00:04:21,427
You are not Datu Rahman.

83
00:04:23,554 --> 00:04:26,057
Who are you? Huh?

84
00:04:26,140 --> 00:04:28,101
Who are you? Tell me who you are!

85
00:04:35,108 --> 00:04:38,111
I will not tell you anything.

86
00:04:38,778 --> 00:04:39,988
[loud thud]

87
00:04:40,655 --> 00:04:42,615
- [objects thudding]
- [Marcus grunting]

88
00:04:44,367 --> 00:04:47,078
[unsettling music continues]

89
00:04:55,878 --> 00:05:01,050
[suspenseful music playing]

90
00:05:07,181 --> 00:05:08,349
Sir!

91
00:05:09,309 --> 00:05:10,393
What's going on?

92
00:05:11,185 --> 00:05:12,103
It's bad.

93
00:05:12,186 --> 00:05:16,024
A new viral video came out.

94
00:05:17,025 --> 00:05:18,484
You're out of the loop again.

95
00:05:21,863 --> 00:05:23,823
[gunshots over video]

96
00:05:26,576 --> 00:05:33,041
[suspenseful music continues]

97
00:05:42,175 --> 00:05:44,469
That damn Datu Rahman!

98
00:05:44,969 --> 00:05:48,681
- He killed Condecido and Vinluan!
- [door clicks shut]

99
00:05:49,182 --> 00:05:51,017
For what? Why?!

100
00:05:51,517 --> 00:05:52,560
For revenge?!

101
00:05:53,394 --> 00:05:56,647
He's the one causing all of our problems!

102
00:05:56,731 --> 00:06:00,276
I'm sure he also killed your comrades.

103
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:02,612
- Lapeña and the others!
- Sir.

104
00:06:04,781 --> 00:06:07,033
We still don't know if the video is real.

105
00:06:13,581 --> 00:06:15,208
[Azuelo] What are you talking
about, Reyes?

106
00:06:16,209 --> 00:06:17,376
This is the proof!

107
00:06:19,378 --> 00:06:21,964
[suspenseful music continues]

108
00:06:28,137 --> 00:06:29,305
Sir, aren't you curious?

109
00:06:30,098 --> 00:06:33,643
That CCTV footage has been
wiped our from our system.

110
00:06:33,726 --> 00:06:36,521
Now, an anonymous user
with an untraceable IP address

111
00:06:36,604 --> 00:06:38,022
uploaded it.

112
00:06:39,398 --> 00:06:41,651
Sir, that could've been done
to change the narrative.

113
00:06:43,945 --> 00:06:46,531
This means that the video is edited,

114
00:06:46,614 --> 00:06:48,157
or it's made by artificial intelligence.

115
00:06:48,241 --> 00:06:51,119
Digital forensics analysis
has been conducted.

116
00:06:51,202 --> 00:06:53,663
- There are no alterations to the video!
- [loud thud]

117
00:06:53,746 --> 00:06:54,872
Sir.

118
00:06:55,373 --> 00:06:57,708
If they managed to penetrate our system

119
00:06:57,792 --> 00:06:59,127
and deleted the CCTV footage,

120
00:06:59,210 --> 00:07:01,587
I'm sure they would have someone

121
00:07:01,671 --> 00:07:03,798
who could've deleted
the alterations as well.

122
00:07:03,881 --> 00:07:07,927
Sir, it's so easy to manipulate
digital evidence now.

123
00:07:08,010 --> 00:07:10,680
Why do you seem so sure

124
00:07:10,763 --> 00:07:13,474
that Datu Rahman isn't really
the one in the video?

125
00:07:14,225 --> 00:07:15,435
Why?

126
00:07:15,518 --> 00:07:16,936
Did you talk to him?

127
00:07:17,019 --> 00:07:20,481
Did you see
that he wasn't there that night?

128
00:07:20,565 --> 00:07:24,152
[music intensifies]

129
00:07:24,235 --> 00:07:25,361
Come with me.

130
00:07:25,987 --> 00:07:26,821
You have to come with me.

131
00:07:26,904 --> 00:07:28,573
I don't want to!

132
00:07:30,116 --> 00:07:32,785
And whatever you're saying
about the video,

133
00:07:32,869 --> 00:07:34,203
about Datu Rahman,

134
00:07:34,287 --> 00:07:37,707
and that theory of yours
that someone is sabotaging us,

135
00:07:37,790 --> 00:07:40,585
it's all a conspiracy theory.

136
00:07:40,668 --> 00:07:42,420
Because you have no basis!

137
00:07:43,337 --> 00:07:44,547
Sir.

138
00:07:46,299 --> 00:07:48,217
This is not just a conspiracy theory.

139
00:07:48,801 --> 00:07:51,554
But you still can't show proof,
Agent Reyes!

140
00:07:52,138 --> 00:07:53,806
What do you want me to do?

141
00:07:53,890 --> 00:07:57,059
Ignore what the forensics shows
because of your gut feel?

142
00:07:57,685 --> 00:07:58,895
Why?

143
00:07:58,978 --> 00:08:01,189
Did Datu Rahaman confirm it himself?

144
00:08:01,689 --> 00:08:03,316
Did you talk to him?

145
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:06,027
Who took you

146
00:08:06,110 --> 00:08:07,945
when you were supposed
to be moved to a facility?

147
00:08:09,780 --> 00:08:11,199
What do they want from you?

148
00:08:15,745 --> 00:08:18,581
If you want me to believe you, Reyes,

149
00:08:18,664 --> 00:08:22,710
bring Datu Rahman to me,
so we can finally know the truth!

150
00:08:22,793 --> 00:08:25,546
And if you still don't have any evidence,

151
00:08:26,881 --> 00:08:30,176
then what's on the video is true.

152
00:08:30,259 --> 00:08:32,428
Datu Rahman is a criminal.

153
00:08:33,554 --> 00:08:35,306
[tense music continues]

154
00:08:40,728 --> 00:08:43,064
[music intensifies, concludes]

155
00:08:43,147 --> 00:08:44,565
Oh Allah!

156
00:08:44,649 --> 00:08:46,192
This is scary.

157
00:08:46,275 --> 00:08:47,818
[tense music playing]

158
00:08:47,902 --> 00:08:49,904
It's horrifying! [stomps]

159
00:08:49,987 --> 00:08:51,948
I can't blame Datu Rahman.

160
00:08:52,031 --> 00:08:53,866
If my community is also massacred,

161
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:55,701
I'd for sure make the cops pay too.

162
00:08:55,785 --> 00:08:57,912
But I thought he was innocent?

163
00:08:58,579 --> 00:09:00,331
Because of what he's done,

164
00:09:00,414 --> 00:09:03,751
he's only proving to them
that he's a criminal.

165
00:09:04,335 --> 00:09:07,505
But we're not yet sure
that it was really him in the video.

166
00:09:07,588 --> 00:09:09,507
What do you mean, Kakah?

167
00:09:09,590 --> 00:09:12,802
Look, it was clearly him.

168
00:09:12,885 --> 00:09:14,303
It's Datu Rahman.

169
00:09:14,387 --> 00:09:17,014
Maybe it's just someone
who looks like him.

170
00:09:17,098 --> 00:09:18,558
[Rashid] Guys, guys.

171
00:09:18,641 --> 00:09:19,642
Listen to me.

172
00:09:20,142 --> 00:09:23,437
You can't just believe anything
you see on the internet.

173
00:09:24,105 --> 00:09:25,982
He's right. Think of it, guys.

174
00:09:26,065 --> 00:09:27,483
It's Datu Rahman we're talking about.

175
00:09:27,567 --> 00:09:30,486
Take it easy on the judgments.

176
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:34,073
He's right. Enough with the chitchat.

177
00:09:34,156 --> 00:09:36,576
[Omar] I've been friends
with Rahman for a long time.

178
00:09:36,659 --> 00:09:38,327
He won't do that.

179
00:09:38,411 --> 00:09:42,331
Especially those aren't the cops
who attacked the people on their island.

180
00:09:43,165 --> 00:09:44,500
Omar.

181
00:09:45,042 --> 00:09:47,044
What about Jamilah?

182
00:09:47,128 --> 00:09:50,089
She'll be devastated
if she learns about that.

183
00:09:50,590 --> 00:09:55,303
[tense music continues]

184
00:09:55,386 --> 00:09:56,762
[host 1] <i>That Datu Rahman is an animal.</i>

185
00:09:56,846 --> 00:09:58,889
<i>Guys, look!</i>

186
00:09:59,473 --> 00:10:00,766
<i>See for yourselves!</i>

187
00:10:00,850 --> 00:10:03,519
<i>Look how shameless he is!</i>

188
00:10:03,603 --> 00:10:06,397
[host 2] <i>You're right.</i>
<i>What are the cops doing?</i>

189
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:09,609
<i>Send him to jail</i>
<i>before he kills more people!</i>

190
00:10:09,692 --> 00:10:12,445
[tense unsettling music playing]

191
00:10:12,528 --> 00:10:13,362
Nurse?

192
00:10:15,906 --> 00:10:16,949
[gasps]

193
00:10:17,033 --> 00:10:20,161
[in English] Uh… It's 130/80.

194
00:10:20,244 --> 00:10:22,788
Is the baby and I okay? Is that too high?

195
00:10:24,415 --> 00:10:26,042
It's a bit on the borderline.

196
00:10:26,125 --> 00:10:28,252
But maybe it's just the heat

197
00:10:28,336 --> 00:10:29,879
and fatigue from traveling.

198
00:10:29,962 --> 00:10:31,380
But we'll have you checked
from time to time.

199
00:10:31,464 --> 00:10:33,299
I'll just get you some water.

200
00:10:37,345 --> 00:10:38,346
Yes, Doc?

201
00:10:38,429 --> 00:10:40,014
Monitor the patient on bed three.

202
00:10:40,097 --> 00:10:42,600
If the fever didn't subside
with IV paracetamol,

203
00:10:42,683 --> 00:10:43,893
call a pediatrician.

204
00:10:43,976 --> 00:10:45,853
[in English] Copy, Doc.
I'll update the charts.

205
00:10:45,936 --> 00:10:51,108
[tense music continues]

206
00:10:53,527 --> 00:10:54,445
Marcus!

207
00:10:57,740 --> 00:10:58,783
Marcus.

208
00:10:59,283 --> 00:11:00,117
‪[sighs]

209
00:11:01,160 --> 00:11:02,578
You just came from Azuelo?

210
00:11:03,496 --> 00:11:05,498
What happened? What did you talk about?

211
00:11:06,248 --> 00:11:07,375
[sighs] Oh.

212
00:11:08,584 --> 00:11:09,585
Nothing. Uh…

213
00:11:10,252 --> 00:11:12,004
[in English] It's nothing important.

214
00:11:15,674 --> 00:11:16,509
‪[music intensifies]

215
00:11:17,843 --> 00:11:18,886
Marcus.

216
00:11:19,470 --> 00:11:20,638
Let's talk.

217
00:11:21,555 --> 00:11:22,765
A serious talk.

218
00:11:22,848 --> 00:11:25,267
[in English] Not like this thing
we've been doing all week.

219
00:11:26,018 --> 00:11:27,478
What do you mean?

220
00:11:28,437 --> 00:11:30,272
Let's be real, Marcus.

221
00:11:30,940 --> 00:11:32,233
Do you have a problem with me?

222
00:11:33,275 --> 00:11:35,027
[in English] Is that why
you've been distant?

223
00:11:35,861 --> 00:11:36,946
Where did that come from?

224
00:11:39,156 --> 00:11:40,366
Lara,

225
00:11:41,659 --> 00:11:44,370
I'm sorry. There's just a lot
on my plate right now.

226
00:11:45,746 --> 00:11:48,582
You know the agency is in shambles lately.

227
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,460
[in English] It's nothing personal.

228
00:11:52,253 --> 00:11:53,337
Okay?

229
00:12:03,931 --> 00:12:05,891
- [door clicks shut]
- [sighs]

230
00:12:05,975 --> 00:12:08,102
- [tense music playing]
- [Jamilah breathing sharply]

231
00:12:10,521 --> 00:12:12,106
[Jamilah sobbing, sniffling]

232
00:12:21,824 --> 00:12:23,075
- [Theresa] Jamilah.
- [sobs]

233
00:12:26,787 --> 00:12:28,038
[sobs]

234
00:12:28,622 --> 00:12:29,748
[sniffles] Uh…

235
00:12:29,832 --> 00:12:32,877
You've been here for a while.
Are you alright?

236
00:12:34,670 --> 00:12:36,213
[voice breaking] I'm okay.

237
00:12:37,089 --> 00:12:41,677
I know you're not, but that's fine.

238
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:45,347
We can't really be strong all the time.

239
00:12:46,599 --> 00:12:49,185
Are you sad because of…

240
00:12:50,519 --> 00:12:53,147
the viral video about Datu Rahman?

241
00:12:53,230 --> 00:12:55,608
[foreboding music playing]

242
00:12:55,691 --> 00:12:57,443
He's your dad, isn't he?

243
00:13:00,070 --> 00:13:02,448
As the head of the department,

244
00:13:02,531 --> 00:13:06,869
it is my responsibility to know
the background of my staff.

245
00:13:06,952 --> 00:13:10,331
I know you're not denying
that Datu Rahman is your father.

246
00:13:11,290 --> 00:13:14,043
But you're also keeping it private, right?

247
00:13:14,126 --> 00:13:17,421
[music turns somber]

248
00:13:17,505 --> 00:13:18,797
Don't worry.

249
00:13:20,299 --> 00:13:22,801
I won't judge your father,

250
00:13:22,885 --> 00:13:25,930
because the case is still ongoing, right?

251
00:13:27,097 --> 00:13:29,058
[sobbing]

252
00:13:31,310 --> 00:13:32,853
Thank you very much.

253
00:13:33,854 --> 00:13:35,064
But I'm asking you.

254
00:13:36,690 --> 00:13:40,444
Please don't judge
my son as a murderer either,

255
00:13:40,528 --> 00:13:42,446
because he's not a bad person.

256
00:13:46,867 --> 00:13:49,578
We're going through the same thing, so…

257
00:13:51,205 --> 00:13:54,667
I know you understand what I'm asking.

258
00:13:56,502 --> 00:13:58,087
[sobs, breathes deeply]

259
00:13:59,880 --> 00:14:00,881
Okay.

260
00:14:01,799 --> 00:14:04,218
[somber music playing]

261
00:14:07,638 --> 00:14:09,473
[sobbing]

262
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:14,979
[unsettling music playing]

263
00:14:16,605 --> 00:14:17,815
Watch this.

264
00:14:20,609 --> 00:14:22,069
- [man on video] <i>Hey!</i>
- [gunshots]

265
00:14:28,659 --> 00:14:31,412
Do you know that people
are cursing you right now

266
00:14:32,329 --> 00:14:34,039
because of that video?

267
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:38,377
It's spreading, and people
are saying you're a murderer,

268
00:14:38,878 --> 00:14:40,129
a criminal.

269
00:14:41,964 --> 00:14:43,007
[scoffs]

270
00:14:43,090 --> 00:14:45,801
Whoever made this video

271
00:14:45,885 --> 00:14:48,053
is feeding you to the public.

272
00:14:50,264 --> 00:14:51,640
But why?

273
00:14:52,516 --> 00:14:53,601
For what?

274
00:14:56,186 --> 00:14:58,564
Did they get you to be the fall guy?

275
00:15:02,234 --> 00:15:03,402
[exhales sharply]

276
00:15:03,485 --> 00:15:04,945
[loud thud]

277
00:15:06,071 --> 00:15:08,073
[exhales sharply]

278
00:15:08,157 --> 00:15:12,995
[breathes deeply]

279
00:15:15,080 --> 00:15:17,082
[music intensifies]

280
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:25,716
Here's the water.

281
00:15:25,799 --> 00:15:27,676
Oh, Rashid.

282
00:15:28,260 --> 00:15:30,846
I noticed you haven't been
traveling for a few days.

283
00:15:30,930 --> 00:15:32,598
Business is slow.

284
00:15:33,223 --> 00:15:34,308
I think

285
00:15:34,391 --> 00:15:37,019
they cancel the booking
when they see that my name

286
00:15:37,102 --> 00:15:38,270
sounds Muslim.

287
00:15:38,354 --> 00:15:39,396
What?

288
00:15:41,231 --> 00:15:42,524
Oh, Nadia,

289
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:45,235
why don't I see your posts anymore?

290
00:15:45,319 --> 00:15:46,528
Is it because of--

291
00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:48,072
It's getting annoying.

292
00:15:48,155 --> 00:15:51,116
In my comment section, they call me…

293
00:15:51,784 --> 00:15:52,993
"tempered glass queen".

294
00:15:53,077 --> 00:15:55,245
- Oh my!
- Same here.

295
00:15:55,329 --> 00:15:57,331
Just over there, near the exit,

296
00:15:57,414 --> 00:16:00,876
whenever I pass by,
they shout, "Terrorist!"

297
00:16:01,460 --> 00:16:02,419
Does that happen to you too?

298
00:16:03,420 --> 00:16:05,589
Ever since the video of Datu Rahman

299
00:16:05,673 --> 00:16:07,049
killing two police officers spread?

300
00:16:07,633 --> 00:16:08,509
Yes.

301
00:16:09,009 --> 00:16:10,219
Same here.

302
00:16:10,719 --> 00:16:13,013
Alright, that's enough.

303
00:16:13,639 --> 00:16:15,182
Always remember,

304
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:18,435
there is always hope. Just keep fighting!

305
00:16:18,519 --> 00:16:19,603
Sit down for a bit.

306
00:16:19,687 --> 00:16:23,482
Here, have some hot soup,
so you can feel a little better.

307
00:16:23,565 --> 00:16:24,733
- Go on.
- That's better.

308
00:16:24,817 --> 00:16:26,276
- You sit here, Nadia.
- Eat up.

309
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:28,654
- Thank you, thank you.
- Come on, eat.

310
00:16:32,533 --> 00:16:34,076
[locker creaking]

311
00:16:40,916 --> 00:16:42,584
[unsettling music playing]

312
00:16:47,006 --> 00:16:49,925
[man] <i>Boss. This looks like the man</i>
<i>you're looking for.</i>

313
00:16:50,009 --> 00:16:51,510
<i>And I found out something.</i>

314
00:16:51,593 --> 00:16:53,178
<i>He is Datu Rahman's son.</i>

315
00:16:59,101 --> 00:17:00,102
[shouts]

316
00:17:03,480 --> 00:17:06,525
[Felix] <i>You're owing me more and more.</i>

317
00:17:07,526 --> 00:17:09,903
<i>I will find you.</i>

318
00:17:09,987 --> 00:17:11,280
<i>You bastard.</i>

319
00:17:15,659 --> 00:17:17,119
[phone buzzing]

320
00:17:18,412 --> 00:17:21,081
Hello? Who is this?

321
00:17:24,001 --> 00:17:26,045
[tense music playing]

322
00:17:26,128 --> 00:17:28,756
Is that so? Alright, thank you.

323
00:17:30,799 --> 00:17:33,260
[pensive music playing]

324
00:17:43,687 --> 00:17:44,563
Listen, everyone.

325
00:17:46,231 --> 00:17:48,025
Fix yourselves up.

326
00:17:48,525 --> 00:17:50,444
He's coming.

327
00:17:50,527 --> 00:17:55,074
[stirring music playing]

328
00:18:42,538 --> 00:18:45,249
Buddy, just be patient.

329
00:18:45,332 --> 00:18:47,292
Datu Rahman will break eventually.

330
00:18:47,376 --> 00:18:50,295
[tense music continues]

331
00:18:53,423 --> 00:18:54,341
Thank you, buddy.

332
00:18:54,424 --> 00:18:56,844
If you need anything, just tell me.

333
00:18:58,971 --> 00:19:01,557
[unsettling music playing]

334
00:19:01,640 --> 00:19:03,100
Are you doing that on purpose?

335
00:19:09,773 --> 00:19:13,861
[music intensifies]

336
00:19:13,944 --> 00:19:20,909
[tense music continues]

337
00:19:20,993 --> 00:19:22,870
[in Arabic] Peace be upon you…

338
00:19:23,912 --> 00:19:25,581
Jalil Abubakar.

339
00:19:26,915 --> 00:19:28,959
Do you know who I am?

340
00:19:30,460 --> 00:19:33,297
I am Mustapha.

341
00:19:34,798 --> 00:19:38,177
Ahmad Mustapha.

342
00:19:46,143 --> 00:19:47,936
What do you want from me?

343
00:19:49,521 --> 00:19:51,106
[sighs]

344
00:19:53,066 --> 00:19:54,860
I want to know…

345
00:19:56,153 --> 00:19:57,946
what happened.

346
00:19:58,572 --> 00:20:00,073
What really happened

347
00:20:00,157 --> 00:20:02,201
on your island.

348
00:20:02,284 --> 00:20:04,620
[tense music playing]

349
00:20:08,957 --> 00:20:10,459
Someone suddenly fired his gun.

350
00:20:12,211 --> 00:20:15,756
And then the members
of the task force suddenly came.

351
00:20:18,467 --> 00:20:20,552
They rained down bullets on us.

352
00:20:20,636 --> 00:20:22,512
- [gunshots]
- [people screaming]

353
00:20:23,513 --> 00:20:26,350
I was surrounded by corpses.

354
00:20:26,433 --> 00:20:29,311
[Jalil] <i>Our island was in flames.</i>

355
00:20:30,395 --> 00:20:32,981
Many of our people died.

356
00:20:35,108 --> 00:20:37,486
Many of us lost our loved ones.

357
00:20:38,111 --> 00:20:40,239
- [gunshots]
- [people screaming]

358
00:20:40,322 --> 00:20:41,949
[Jalil] Run! Just run!

359
00:20:42,032 --> 00:20:43,951
- [people screaming]
- [gunshots]

360
00:20:44,034 --> 00:20:44,868
[people screaming]

361
00:20:44,952 --> 00:20:47,996
[coughing]

362
00:20:53,418 --> 00:20:55,420
They didn't stop shooting.

363
00:20:57,881 --> 00:20:59,549
That's until they caught Amah.

364
00:21:00,592 --> 00:21:03,971
[suspenseful music playing]

365
00:21:05,681 --> 00:21:11,186
If you only saw how scared
the kids were from what they saw,

366
00:21:11,937 --> 00:21:16,400
then you'd understand why
I'd do anything in my power

367
00:21:16,483 --> 00:21:18,902
to give them justice.

368
00:21:19,903 --> 00:21:22,114
That shouldn't have happened to us.

369
00:21:23,282 --> 00:21:25,784
We didn't do anything wrong.

370
00:21:28,036 --> 00:21:29,371
We were living in peace,

371
00:21:29,454 --> 00:21:33,166
but they ruined our lives!

372
00:21:35,335 --> 00:21:36,712
Who are you referring to?

373
00:21:37,462 --> 00:21:40,465
I don't have proof yet, but I'm certain.

374
00:21:41,300 --> 00:21:44,553
The person behind it works for NLEA.

375
00:21:44,636 --> 00:21:47,055
They also abducted Amah!

376
00:21:47,639 --> 00:21:50,225
Same with the people who abducted us.

377
00:21:50,726 --> 00:21:53,270
That's why I need to get inside them,

378
00:21:54,938 --> 00:21:57,232
so I can find out the truth.

379
00:22:00,193 --> 00:22:02,154
So I can also save Amah.

380
00:22:11,663 --> 00:22:13,248
I believe you.

381
00:22:16,418 --> 00:22:17,836
I'll help you.

382
00:22:20,672 --> 00:22:24,801
Whoever is behind all of this…

383
00:22:25,635 --> 00:22:30,891
I'm sure that you're neither
their first nor last victim.

384
00:22:33,101 --> 00:22:35,729
We need to stop them.

385
00:22:36,855 --> 00:22:41,693
As soon as possible.

386
00:22:44,362 --> 00:22:49,201
I'll get you inside NLEA
as a liaison officer.

387
00:22:49,951 --> 00:22:53,330
[Ahmad] <i>I'll give you good credentials</i>

388
00:22:53,997 --> 00:22:55,624
<i>and a clean background.</i>

389
00:22:55,707 --> 00:22:59,711
<i>I'll get you in as an honorable,</i>

390
00:23:00,337 --> 00:23:01,671
<i>clean,</i>

391
00:23:01,755 --> 00:23:05,300
<i>and good cop from Mindanao.</i>

392
00:23:07,511 --> 00:23:08,762
From now on,

393
00:23:10,097 --> 00:23:12,349
you will work for me.

394
00:23:12,974 --> 00:23:14,559
I want to know

395
00:23:14,643 --> 00:23:18,563
what's going on inside and outside

396
00:23:18,647 --> 00:23:21,608
of NLEA and SID.

397
00:23:21,691 --> 00:23:25,946
All their secrets, discussions, and plans.

398
00:23:30,408 --> 00:23:31,451
But why me?

399
00:23:33,286 --> 00:23:34,579
[chuckles] Because…

400
00:23:35,831 --> 00:23:41,419
Because you're the most useful.

401
00:23:42,003 --> 00:23:43,255
[in English] You have nothing to lose.

402
00:23:43,338 --> 00:23:45,257
[in English] You have everything to gain!

403
00:23:46,341 --> 00:23:49,719
I know that you're now desperate

404
00:23:50,220 --> 00:23:51,888
to save your father.

405
00:23:51,972 --> 00:23:56,059
You desperately want to know the truth.

406
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:59,604
Jalil, we both want the same thing.

407
00:24:02,149 --> 00:24:04,067
But keep this in mind.

408
00:24:05,527 --> 00:24:07,571
When you walk out the door,

409
00:24:08,071 --> 00:24:09,656
you are on your own.

410
00:24:11,741 --> 00:24:15,203
But if you get caught and your identity

411
00:24:15,871 --> 00:24:17,873
gets revealed,

412
00:24:19,082 --> 00:24:23,211
I will disavow any knowledge of you.

413
00:24:23,295 --> 00:24:26,256
[in English] I will deny everything.

414
00:24:26,339 --> 00:24:28,550
Jalil, you'll be on your own.

415
00:24:29,759 --> 00:24:31,595
Remember this, Jalil.

416
00:24:32,095 --> 00:24:34,097
We don't know each other.

417
00:24:34,181 --> 00:24:37,309
Only the two of us will know about this.

418
00:24:37,392 --> 00:24:39,519
Do you understand?

419
00:24:39,603 --> 00:24:42,272
[foreboding music continues]

420
00:24:46,526 --> 00:24:47,652
[Jalil, in English] Yes, sir.

421
00:24:50,071 --> 00:24:51,114
From now on,

422
00:24:51,823 --> 00:24:56,661
you are now Police Major Allan Espina.

423
00:25:01,541 --> 00:25:05,587
[foreboding music continues]

424
00:25:06,171 --> 00:25:07,380
[in English] Yes, sir.

425
00:25:10,842 --> 00:25:12,093
[in Arabic] May peace be upon you.

426
00:25:14,346 --> 00:25:17,224
[in Arabic] May Allah
have mercy and bless you.

427
00:25:21,061 --> 00:25:22,854
[foreboding music continues]

428
00:25:22,938 --> 00:25:23,813
[exhales]

429
00:25:37,369 --> 00:25:38,828
[Azuelo] <i>Major Allan Espina.</i>

430
00:25:38,912 --> 00:25:41,581
Welcome to the Special
Investigations Division.

431
00:25:42,999 --> 00:25:44,167
[Marcus] <i>Did you bump</i>
<i>into me intentionally?</i>

432
00:25:44,251 --> 00:25:46,586
You're the one who bumped into me.

433
00:25:47,087 --> 00:25:52,259
[Ahmad] <i>They handle all the gun-smuggling</i>
<i>cases in the country.</i>

434
00:25:52,342 --> 00:25:55,345
<i>You'll stay close to them</i>
<i>and befriend them.</i>

435
00:25:55,428 --> 00:25:58,056
Agent Marcus Reyes, I'm excited
to be working with you.

436
00:25:58,139 --> 00:26:02,519
You will get all the information we need.

437
00:26:02,602 --> 00:26:04,688
[Lara] <i>Why can't I have access</i>
<i>to your records?</i>

438
00:26:04,771 --> 00:26:06,523
<i>What are you hiding, Espina?</i>

439
00:26:06,606 --> 00:26:09,818
<i>Are you a deep cover agent?</i>

440
00:26:09,901 --> 00:26:10,986
What are you doing here?

441
00:26:11,069 --> 00:26:15,532
I want to know everything behind
the massacre on the island.

442
00:26:15,615 --> 00:26:17,826
Those are my team's files.
You just can't meddle with it!

443
00:26:17,909 --> 00:26:19,703
What will happen now?
I already touched it.

444
00:26:19,786 --> 00:26:22,163
[Marcus] <i>I know you've been</i>
<i>following us since earlier.</i>

445
00:26:22,247 --> 00:26:23,873
<i>What do you need from me?</i>

446
00:26:23,957 --> 00:26:24,833
<i>Make no mistake.</i>

447
00:26:24,916 --> 00:26:27,127
- Or I'll fire my gun!
- [Jalil] <i>I'll also fire mine.</i>
